U-Net SCAT & VSAT, 151 images, 192x96 pixels

The Data Set

We’ll use the MRI dataset. It’s a set of 102 training images, plus 10 test images with manually segmented SCAT and 10 test images with manually segmented VSAT.

plot_channels <- function(chList, k) {
  plot_array2d(chList[[k]][2:3], names(chList)[[k]], title_size = 10)
}
plot_pred <- function(image_tensor, pred_list, k, ch = 2) {
  plot2_array2d(
    image_tensor[k,,,1], pred_list[[k]][[ch]],
    alpha = 0.15, title = names(pred_list)[[k]], title_size = 10
  )
}

Create the Unet model

model <- createUnetModel2D(
  inputImageSize = c(dim(image_train[1,,,1]), 1),
  numberOfOutputs = 3L, # numberOfLabels
  numberOfLayers = 3,
  numberOfFiltersAtBaseLayer = 48L,
  convolutionKernelSize = c(3, 3),
  deconvolutionKernelSize = c(2, 2),
  poolSize = c(2, 2),
  strides = c(2, 2),
  dropoutRate = 0.1,
  # weightDecay = 0.0001,
  # addAttentionGating = TRUE,
  mode = "classification"
)

cat(
  "Trainable params: ",
  formatC(model$count_params(), big.mark=","),
  "\n"
)
#> Trainable params:  1,047,699

Compile the Unet model

model %>% compile(
  loss = loss_multilabel_dice,
  optimizer = optimizer_adam(lr = 0.0001),
  metrics = metric_multilabel_dice
)

Fit the Unet model

track <- model %>% fit(
  image_train, fat_train,
  epochs = 44,
  batch_size = 1,
  validation_split = 0.1, verbose = 1, shuffle = TRUE,
  callbacks = list(
    callback_model_checkpoint(
      "hdf5/unet_model_fat_interim_weights.h5",
      monitor = 'val_loss',
      save_best_only = TRUE
    ),
    callback_reduce_lr_on_plateau(
      monitor = "val_loss",
      factor = 0.1
    )
  )
)
plot_history(track)

Evaluate the Unet model

model %>% evaluate(image_test, fat_test)
#> $loss
#> [1] 0.1289
#> 
#> $mdice_coef
#> [1] 0.8711

(Multiple) Dice Coefficient

\[ \begin{align*} \rm smoothing\ factor &= 1\cr \rm union\ overlap &= \cfrac{\rm intersection}{\rm sum}\cr \rm dice\ coeff &= \cfrac{\rm 2\cdot union\ overlap + smoothing\ factor} {\rm 1 + union\ overlap + smoothing\ factor} \end{align*} \]

From the dice coefficient definition we get

\[ \begin{align*} \rm union\ overlap&= \frac{ \rm dice\ coeff - smoothing\ factor\cdot(1 - dice\ coeff)} {\rm 2 - dice\ coeff} \end{align*} \]

Simple check.

dice_coefficient(0)
#> [1] 0.5
union_overlap(0.5)
#> [1] 0
dcoeff <- c(0.5, 0.6, 0.7, 0.8, 0.9, 1)
union_overlap(dcoeff)
#> [1] 0.0000 0.1429 0.3077 0.5000 0.7273 1.0000
dcoeff2 <- c(0.95, 0.96, 0.97, 0.98, 0.99, 1)
union_overlap(dcoeff2)
#> [1] 0.8571 0.8846 0.9126 0.9412 0.9703 1.0000
dcoeff3 <- c(0.995, 0.996, 0.997, 0.998, 0.999, 1)
union_overlap(dcoeff3)
#> [1] 0.9851 0.9880 0.9910 0.9940 0.9970 1.0000
dcoeff4 <- c(0.9995, 0.9996, 0.9997, 0.9998, 0.9999, 1)
union_overlap(dcoeff4)
#> [1] 0.9985 0.9988 0.9991 0.9994 0.9997 1.0000
